One person has been killed following gun attacks by unknown gunmen in Ogbunabali community in Port Harcourt City Local Government Area of Rivers State. DAILY POST gathered that the sporadic shooting which happened on Friday lasted for an hour, leading to the death of a man identified as Obinna Chima Nwogbu. Chima-Nwogbu who hailed from Rumuji community in Emohua Local Government Area of the state was hit by a bullet but was said not to be the target of the gunmen. While the remains of the victim is still at the scene of the attack at the time of filing this report, the Rivers State Police Command is yet to issue a statement about the incident. ESN commander didn’t die in gun battle with Army – IPOB clarifies 